FBIS4-65638 "drweu098_o_94004" FBIS-WEU-94-098 Daily Report 19 May 1994 CYPRUS Poll Shows Europeans Support EU Membership Poll Shows Europeans Support EU Membership NC1905191494 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network in Greek 1600 GMT 19 May 94 NC1905191494 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network Greek BFN [Text] The majority of the peoples in the European Union [EU] support a quick accession of Cyprus to the Union. A poll conducted for the EU last February and made public today shows that 53 percent of the Europeans in the poll support the quick accession of Cyprus, 35 percent were against, and 12 percent did not express an opinion. Regarding Turkey, the poll had a negative result: 43 percent of those asked were in favor of Turkey's accession and 48 percent were against. Of those in favor of Cyprus' accession, first were the Greeks, then the Irish, followed by the Spaniards and British.
